snippet.textDisplay:
I like what I see. Mikel has great positive energy and its good to see that he balances that well with ruthlessness.

If I could pass on a message to Mikel, I'd say I want Arsenal to remember what made them Invincibles - a complete team, built from a SOLID defence to a STRONG and CREATIVE midfield, and an attack with FLAIR and INSTINCT and incredible quality. If we are to get back to that, we need to learn to love defending as much as any other part of the game. To not be afraid of making tackles. Not be afraid of playing risky forward passes. We're already blessed with quality attacking players. What's clearly missing is the solid defending and strength and creativity in midfield. While the young players provide some of the workrate and attacking flair, they cannot be relied upon to change the outcome of a match. And so we need to address the deficiencies of the squad with replacing some of the poor quality in defence and midfield and UPGRADE. Thats not completely up to Mikel. I hope the club supports him because theres no way we're going to be fighting for trophies if something so obvious as the poor defence and weak midfield is something that they don't see. It's not acceptable that we can't sign better defenders and midfielders than teams like Wolves, Watford, West Ham, Newcastle, Sheffield Utd, Bournemouth, Leiscester.
